!pragma layout smetana
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam nodesep 80
skinparam ranksep 80
title CLS-04 - Invarianti strutturali e GrantConstraintPolicy
skinparam shadowing false
hide empty members

class ACLEntryInvariants <<DomainPolicy>> {
  +validate(entry, operation_spec) : void
  +INV_1_has_level_or_group()
  +INV_2_no_anonymous_mutating_allow()
  +INV_3_valid_level_and_group()
  +INV_4_valid_joins()
  +INV_5_no_public_subject_or()
  +INV_6_global_and_roots_need_global_manage()
  +INV_7_protected_grants_checked()
}

interface GrantConstraintPolicy {
  +validate_grant(caller, entry, operation_spec) : void
}

class ACLService {
  +create_entry(identity, input)
  +update_entry(identity, entry_id, changes)
  +replace_entries(identity, resource, inputs)
}

class OperationSpec {
  +protected : bool
  +read_only : bool
}

class ACLValidationError
class GrantConstraintError

ACLService --> ACLEntryInvariants
ACLService --> GrantConstraintPolicy : se ALLOW protected
ACLEntryInvariants --> OperationSpec
ACLEntryInvariants ..> ACLValidationError
GrantConstraintPolicy ..> GrantConstraintError

note right of GrantConstraintPolicy
  Limita cosa puo essere concesso:
  operazioni possedute, protected globali,
  soglie non piu privilegiate del chiamante.
end note

legend
  Vedi anche: [[../attivit%C3%A0/05_creazione_entry_acl.puml ACT-05]] |
  [[../attivit%C3%A0/09_grant_protetti.puml ACT-09]] |
  [[../use%20case/06_gestire_profili_grant_protetti.puml UC-06]]
endlegend
@enduml
